    <h1>A grow&#xAD;ing voice</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200720/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-07-20"><time>2020-07-20</time></a>
        - <span>SPORT</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>2003</p>
    <p>The Sin­ga­pore Na­tional Olympic Coun­cil (SNOC) sets up a pro­tem ath­letes’ com­mis­sion, headed by for­mer na­tional sailor Dr Ben Tan. It is made of­fi­cial two years later.</p>
    <p>2013</p>
    <p>The Republic hosts the In­ter­na­tional Olympic Com­mit­tee (IOC) In­ter­na­tional Ath­letes’ Fo­rum, where is­sues rang­ing from dop­ing to ath­letes’ roles in the Olympic move­ment were dis­cussed in a di­a­logue fea­tur­ing sports­men and women, some on the IOC’s ath­lete com­mis­sion.</p>
    <p>2014</p>
    <p>The Sin­ga­pore Swim­ming As­so­ci­a­tion forms its ath­letes’ com­mis­sion. Rus­sell Ong is its first chair­man.</p>
    <p>2017</p>
    <p>Na­tional fencer Sam­son Lee is the first Sin­ga­porean elected as a mem­ber of the Fenc­ing Con­fed­er­a­tion of Asia ath­letes’ com­mis­sion.</p>
    <p>2018</p>
    <p>Archer Syahi­dah Alim is voted into the Asian Par­a­lympic Com­mit­tee’s seven-per­son ath­letes’ com­mit­tee.</p>
    <p>2018</p>
    <p>Na­tional sports as­so­ci­a­tions (NSAs) for sev­eral sports such as bad­minton, silat and table ten­nis set up ath­letes’ com­mis­sions.</p>

